---
title: Italian Ciabatta Burgers with Mozzarella Cheese and Sweet-and-Tangy Salad
description: We’ve taken an American classic and given it an Italian makeover by swapping out traditional buns for ciabatta bread. Your whole family will love the crusty outside and irresistibly soft inside. Plus, it’s hearty enough to hold the juicy patties, gooey cheese, and refreshing greens.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/italian-ciabatta-burger-family-95d96cd6.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/italian-ciabatta-burger-family-fa6e8410.pdf
nutrition:
  calories: 725 kcal
  fat: 32 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 60 g
  sugar: 6 g
  protein: 46 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 800 mg
cuisine: North America
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/italian-ciabatta-burger-family-57c9b22377d68d7f0d8b4568
servings: 2
time required: 30 minutes
author: Michelle Doll Olson
---

Wash and dry all produce. Preheat the #oven{} to 400 degrees. Halve, peel, and thinly slice the @red onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced). Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{10%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium heat. Add the onion and @sugar{2%teaspoon}. Cook, tossing, for ~{6-8%minutes}, until caramelized. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove from the pan and set aside.

> TIP: For a bolder flavor, add 1 Tablespoon balsamic vinegar to the pan after the onions are caramelized, then reduce until syrupy.

Mince or grate @garlic{2%clove}(minced or grated 1/2 teaspoon). In a large #bowl{}, whisk together 1 Tablespoon @tomato paste{6%ounce}, 2 Tablespoons @balsamic vinegar{2%tablespoon}, 2 Tablespoons olive oil, and as much of the garlic as you like. Season with salt and pepper.

Form the @ground beef{20%ounce} into two patties, and season on both sides with salt and pepper. In the same pan, heat a large drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Add the patties. Cook ~{2-4%minutes} per side, until almost cooked to desired doneness. Top with @mozzarella cheese{1%cup}. Cover the pan for another ~{1%minute}, until the cheese melts.

Toast the ciabatta: While the burgers cook, halve the @ciabatta bread{4}. Place in the oven to toast ~{3-5%minutes}.

Toss the salad: Toss the @mixed greens{4%ounce} into the vinaigrette, and season with salt and pepper.

Place each burger inside a bun, then top with the caramelized onion and a bit of sweet-and-tangy salad. Serve the remaining salad on the side and enjoy!